// Package Used

npm i  -> Install Packages
1. express -> Helps in creating servers easily and managing routes, requests, and responses.

2. dotenv > Keeps sensitive information secure and hidden from code.

3. mongoose -> An ODM (Object Data Modeling) library for MongoDB. 
            Helps you define schemas & models for your database.Makes interacting with MongoDB easier (Course.find(), User.save()).

4. jsonwebtoken -> Used for authentication. Creates and verifies tokens 
                (JWTs) so that users stay logged in securely.

5. nodemon -> A dev tool that automatically restarts your server whenever
             you make changes in your code.

6. cookie-parser -> Middleware to parse cookies attached to client requests.
                    Useful when you store JWTs or session info in cookies.

7. bcryptjs -> A library for hashing and comparing passwords.
                Ensures user passwords are stored securely in your database.

8. validator -> Provides functions to validate and sanitize strings.
                check if an email is valid. 

9. cors -> Stands for Cross-Origin Resource Sharing.
